Rebecca Fyffe, owner of a pest control business in the Chicago area, credits the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA) for helping her expand her business. The SBA assisted Fyffe in developing a business plan, accessing capital, diversifying her customer base, and securing federal contracts. Fyffe was recognized as the 2018 National Small Business Person of the Year. The SBA supports entrepreneurs and small businesses through various resources, such as loans, counseling, training, and assistance in competing for government contracts. The SBA aims to remove barriers and empower small businesses to thrive.